title: Wawawai Landing TT & Wawawai Grade Hill Climb
Tour de Dung #1
description:
Tour De Dung Road Race #1: March 10th 2012.
PRESENTED BY: THE GARAGE AND KRYKISPORTS CYCLING TEAMS
First of two races in the rain shadow of the beautiful Olympic Mountain Range. 
Start/finish is across the road from the Dungeness State Park and Recreation Area
course: COURSE: Very flat fast good surfaced course (2-3 rollers) but wind frequently has been a factor usually out of the west between 10 to 20 mph. Course is the same as in years past. Finish will be on Kitchen Dick Rd.
registration:
RaceDay Registration ONLY: 
Each race $30 which inlcudes Washington State Taxes.
Registration opens at 8:45 AM and closes 15 minutes prior to the start of your race.
Annual USA Cycling Licenses ONLY: One day licenses for Cat 5 Men and Cat 4 Women only.
WSBA numbers: Will be used and can be purchased at www.wsbaracing.com (not for sale at the race).
Rental numbers: Will be available at the race for a $10 rental fee ($5 is refundable). For out-of-state riders there is no fee to rent a number just a $5 deposit.
Masters 50+ can ride either Masters Race
notes:
Parking and porta-lets will be located in the field across the road from the Dungeness State Park and Recreation Area.
RACE NUMBERS: WSBA numbers on the LEFT hand side of jerseys and on frame.
More race and Prize details will be posted closer to event on http://racing.garagebilliards.com/
directions:
LOCATION: Sequim, Dungeness, Washington.
From Seattle using the Bainbridge Island Ferry: Exit the ferry at Winslow. Stay on SR 305 to Poulsbo. Proceed through Poulsbo and take SR 3 north (follow signs to the Hood Canal Bridge). Follow directions from Hood Canal Bridge. 
From the Edmunds-Kingston Ferry: Remain on SR 104 the Canal Bridge. Follow directions from Hood Canal Bridge.
From Tacoma: Take SR 16 from the Tacoma Narrows Bridge north. At the junction with SR 3, take SR 3 north to the Hood Canal Bridge.
Directions from Hood Canal Bridge: At the Hood Canal Bridge, make a left turn (right turn if you are coming from Kingston) and proceed across the bridge (on SR 104). Follow SR 104 to the junction with US Hwy 101. Take US 101 North toward Pt. Townsend and Pt. Angeles. Follow US 101 past Sequim, stay on Highway 101 until you reach Kitchen Dick Road, take a right onto Kitchen Dick Road. Continue on Kitchen Dick Road, past Woodcock when you will be on the race course, all the way to Lotzgesell Road Rd where the parking area and Start/Finish location.
From Olympia and South: Take US Hwy 101 north. Follow US 101 past Sequim, stay on Highway 101 until you reach Kitchen Dick Road, take a right onto Kitchen Dick Road. Continue on Kitchen Dick Road, past Woodcock when you will be on the race course, all the way to Lotzgesell Road Rd where the parking area and Start/Finish location

title: FareStart Time Trial
course: -	9 mile flat course.  The start is at the county line and then you go east on Lowell-Snohomish River Rd towards Snohomish.  The turn-around is just before the overpass.  This is an out-and-back course.
registration:
-	Registration opens at 6:30 AM and closes at 8:30 AM.
-	Registration will be located in the Rotary Park parking lot in Everett, WA on Lowell-Snohomish River Rd which is about 200 m from the start.
-	Cost is $20 to preregister through BikeReg.com.  Day of race is $25 if the race is not sold out.
-	Please take the opportunity to pre-register.  Besides saving a few dollars pre-registering gives you an assigned start time and helps to ensure quick and accurate results.  If you register on the day of the race you will have the last start times.
notes:
Start Time
-	The first rider will start at 9:00 AM.  Riders will leave at 30 second intervals.
-	Start times will be posted on the FareStart Cycling Team race web page by Friday, March 16 and at registration on the day of the race.
-	Start times will be assigned randomly within category.
Multiple Races
-	Want to race multiple times?  Not a problem.  You can race multiple times in your category, in a Masters category or in the Retro category or any combination thereof.
-	If you want to race more than once please contact the race director and we will accommodate you with appropriate start times.
Race Numbers
-	We will NOT be using WSBA numbers.  We will be using event-specific numbers that are sequential to help us with timing and results.
-	If you are racing more than once please don\'t forget to swap your numbers!
directions: 3505 Lowell Snohomish River Rd, Everett, WA 98201

title: Volunteer Park Criterium
description: The first criterium of the 2012 race season.
course: Each lap is .82 of a mile \"U\" shaped loop with 50 feet of climbing on good roads.
registration: Pre-register online and pay $25 vs. $30 day of race.  Pre-register for two races and pay $35 total vs. $40 day of race.
notes:
All USA Cycling rules will be enforced. All riders must sign a waiver and wear an approved helmet.

These races are USA Cycling sanctioned. A USCF license is required. This race is held under USCF Permit # TBD.

* Annual licenses will be unavailable for purchase at the race. Purchase a license prior to race day or purchase one-day license at race registration.
directions:
A) From I-5 Southbound
    Exit at Bolston Ave/Roanoke St (exit #168A)
    Turn Left on E Roanoke St.
    Cross I-5
    Merge into the right lane
    Turn right at 10th Ave E.
    Turn Left onto E Boston Street
    E Boston becomes 15th Ave E.
    The entrance to Volunteer Park will be on your left (approx 1/2 mile from 10th Ave E.)

B) From I-5 Northbound
Take the East Olive Way Exit (exit #166)
Bear right on East Olive Way
East Olive Way merges into East John St
East John comes to a T at 15th Ave E
Turn Left on 15th Ave E.
In about 3/4 of a mile, the entrance to Volunteer Park will be on your left

title: Tour of Walla Walla
description: Stage race with a crit, ind TT and a RR (for 4 upper cats, 2 RRs)
course:
Stage 1- RR for Men Pro-1-2, cat 3 & Mstrs, and Wm Pro-1-2. Distance, elev gain varies by cat.
Stage 2- crit for all cats.
Stage 3- TT, 9.3 miles
Stage 4- RR. Distance, elev gain varies.
registration:
Field limits and fees (not incl online fee of approx $4.50)
Men Pro-1-2 120 riders (115 initially to allow for cat upgrades), $110
Men cat 3 95 (90 initially), $95
Men 4-5 75, $85
Mstrs 40+ cats 1-4 95, $95
Wm Pro-1-2 65 (60 initially), $95
Wm 3 45 (40 initially), $85
Wm 4 45, $85
Jrs, $20 off, refundable at check-in.
50% refund requests by Apr 1
cat changes by Apr 4 ($20 fee)
mail-in reg by Apr 4 (postmark)
reg transfers by Apr 11 ($20 fee)
No late reg, no day of race reg
notes:
Check-in for Men Pro-1-2, Cat 3 & Mstrs, and Wm Pro-1-2 in Waitsburg, WA. Follow signs. Friday 1:00 pm to 1 hr before start.
Check-in for Men Cat 4-5, Wm 3, Wm 4 and Mstr Wm 40+ Friday 9am to 6pm at Allegro Cyclery, 200 E. Main, Walla Walla, WA  or
Saturday 6am to 1 hr before start
directions:
To Friday RR check-in and race start (Men Pro-1-2, Cat 3, Mstrs and Wm Pro-1-2). Waitsburg, WA, follow signs.
To Saturday crit, downtown Walla Walla, WA.

Second Ascent Ballard Criterium
description: The Second Ascent Ballard Criterium is one of Seattles classic bike races with a great city course, lots of fans and a fantastic atmosphere. Just like the original crits in Belgium, the keystone pro event kicks off at 7:30pm with fans spilling out of the local bars and restaurants to watch and cheer.
course: Four corner, ~1km on bumpy city streets with a very slight side hill.
registration:
There are two ways to register: USA Cycling and day of race. 


Day of race registration will open at 2:30pm and close 15 minutes prior to each categorys start time. Registration will be located behind the start/finish truck. USCF license required and can be purchased from USA Cycling. One day USCF license available for Cat 5 mens and Cat 4 womens races only - $10.
notes: All USCF rules will be enforced! All riders must sign a waiver and wear an USCF approved helmet! USCF permit #2012-1495
directions: Ballard, WA (Start/finish at Ballard Ave. NW & 20th Ave. NW)

title: Walla Walla XC Stanger Farm
course: Course on private land. Many fun features, incl triple fly-over, barns, stream crossings and more.
registration: Day of race registration only. Registration opens on site at 9am and closes 15 minutes before each race start. $22 for first race, $12 for each additional race.
notes: Helmets required. No bar-ends allowed. Jrs need parent or guardian to sign waiver. One-day licenses avail at reg for cat 4 men & women. Promoter reserves right to combine or split cats. Series pts detailed at www.emdesports.com.
directions: Hwy 12 to Sapolil Rd (1.1 mi west of Sapolil E Rd), turn north, 1.0 mile to driveway entrance.

title: Walla Walla XC Bennington Lake
course: Grass, gravel, dirt, pavement. Climbing, descending. 1.8-mile loop.
registration: Day of race registration only. Open 9 am to 15 minutes before each race start. $22 for the first race ($12 for Jrs), $12 for each additional race. 18&U require parent/guardian signature on waiver.
notes: Helmets required. No bar-ends allowed. One-day licenses available for cat 4 men and women for $10/day.
directions: Hwy 12 to Tausick Way/Airport Rd exit. Go south to Reservoir Rd. Left a couple miles to parking and registration.

title: Inland NW Cyclocross Series-Walter's Fruit Ran
2012 Washington State Cyclocross Championship
description:
2012 Washington State Cyclocross Championships,
Arlington Airport \"Naval Gun-Sighting Course\", Arlington, WA. Presented by the W.S.B.A. and Bikesport Racing.
course: This will be a brand new course; \" The Naval Gun-Sighting Course\" at the North End of the Arlington Airport, Arlington, WA. We are working on new and challenging improvements over last year\'s course!
registration: Pre-registration will be available via usacycling.org. Like last year, we will be running the championships as a non-profit benefit race so pre-reg and day-of registration will be a flat rate of $25. Pls register for your race at least 45 min prior to start.
notes: At this time we plan on using Seattle Cyclocross race numbers so please keep those handy. We will follow the SCX race schedule as well. Please pack out your trash and clean up your team areas before you leave the site. Thanks!
directions: I-5 to exit 206. East on Hwy 531 to Smokey Point Blvd. Go left (North). Go right on 188th Street NE. Take this to its end at N. Arlington Airport grounds. Looking for gate and parking.
